1
00:00:01,970 --> 00:00:03,110
You should...

2
00:00:03,880 --> 00:00:06,380
marry me, Ji Hyuk.

3
00:00:10,850 --> 00:00:11,880
What?

4
00:00:12,820 --> 00:00:15,220
Marry me.

5
00:00:15,650 --> 00:00:16,820
What got into you?

6
00:00:17,090 --> 00:00:19,620
I'm not asking you to marry me...

7
00:00:19,620 --> 00:00:22,360
because I don't know
you announced to everyone...

8
00:00:22,930 --> 00:00:24,560
that you won't marry.

9
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:27,730
I'm so flabbergasted
that I don't want to respond.

10
00:00:27,730 --> 00:00:29,200
If this is nonsense, quit it.

11
00:00:29,570 --> 00:00:31,670
If you have an ulterior motive,
just say it.

12
00:00:32,470 --> 00:00:34,010
I will respond
after hearing the whole thing.

13
00:00:38,240 --> 00:00:39,840
You know, I've been in love before.

14
00:00:40,650 --> 00:00:42,150
Seriously enough to risk my life.

15
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:46,120
I thought
I'd never be able to forget him.

16
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:49,620
I mean, I loved him so much...

17
00:00:49,790 --> 00:00:52,090
that I decided to stay with him
for the rest of my life.

18
00:00:54,490 --> 00:00:58,160
If I knew where he was,
I'd want to run to him right away.

19
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:01,030
I was in love
that had so many lingering regrets.

20
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:05,440
But just because I love him,
it doesn't mean I can be with him.

21
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:07,270
You know that.

22
00:01:10,410 --> 00:01:12,140
Now that the man I love is gone,

23
00:01:12,810 --> 00:01:14,510
I have no choice
but to give up on love,

24
00:01:15,810 --> 00:01:17,980
but I don't want to give up
the background offered by my father.

25
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:21,790
I think you want...

26
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:25,120
to stay single
because the losses outweigh...

27
00:01:25,290 --> 00:01:26,720
the gains from marriage.

28
00:01:27,160 --> 00:01:28,360
Are you done?

29
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:29,890
I agree with you, Ji Hyuk.

30
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:34,100
Now, I know that
marriage isn't just about love.

31
00:01:34,630 --> 00:01:37,000
That's why I'm suggesting a deal.

32
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:40,640
Why would you refuse to get married
when you could gain a lot from it?

33
00:01:42,170 --> 00:01:44,680
It's not like
I want us to be lovebirds.

34
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,880
But still...

35
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:47,310
You wanted to stay single
because you thought...

36
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:48,480
you wouldn't find someone to love?

37
00:01:49,380 --> 00:01:50,480
That's not it, right?

38
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:53,750
Then there's no reason
not to marry without love.

39
00:01:54,890 --> 00:01:58,720
Besides, you are not
the type of person who loves anyone.

40
00:01:59,690 --> 00:02:01,790
You say
you can control your feelings.

41
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:08,970
What is it that...

42
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:11,940
I get from this marriage
at this point?

43
00:02:14,370 --> 00:02:16,740
Should I start
negotiating or something?

44
00:02:16,980 --> 00:02:18,740
I'm the only daughter
of the Haneul Construction family.

45
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:20,950
My father, CEO Jung Ho Yeong,

46
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:23,550
has his ironclad rule
of not letting a woman...

47
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,880
take over control of the company.

48
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:28,050
You are already aware of that.

49
00:02:28,150 --> 00:02:29,790
Because there were
rumors going around.

50
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,760
And who knows?

51
00:02:33,730 --> 00:02:35,190
We might develop feelings
for each other...

52
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:36,390
while living together.

53
00:02:37,630 --> 00:02:39,360
Then we could be a real couple.

54
00:02:39,930 --> 00:02:41,000
Or...

55
00:02:42,070 --> 00:02:43,170
we could get a divorce.

56
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:45,070
After my father passes away.

57
00:02:46,170 --> 00:02:49,040
I don't know
when that will be, though.

58
00:02:51,740 --> 00:02:53,340
Aren't you laying your cards
on the table too easily?

59
00:02:54,150 --> 00:02:55,650
So, you know
that I'm not just saying this.

60
00:02:56,980 --> 00:02:58,950
I'll give you some time
to think about it, then.

61
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:01,520
I'll see you here next week.

62
00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:20,510
(Episode 4)

63
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:23,140
I've never seen anything like that
in my life.

64
00:03:35,820 --> 00:03:36,890
Hello, Father.

65
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:40,560
Ji Hyuk, do you have plans
for tonight after work?

66
00:03:42,390 --> 00:03:44,130
You knew?

67
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:47,900
No. I don't have any plans.

68
00:03:48,230 --> 00:03:50,900
Then meet me outside after work.

69
00:03:51,140 --> 00:03:52,240
Where should I go?

70
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:54,570
Should I go to Mr. Yeong Bo's place?

71
00:03:55,670 --> 00:03:57,180
- Here.
- Hey.

72
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:58,410
I'll pour my own drink.

73
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:00,280
Don't take the fun away from me.

74
00:04:00,350 --> 00:04:01,980
We haven't done this
for a long time.

75
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:04,550
I know.

76
00:04:06,380 --> 00:04:07,420
All right.

77
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:10,760
Gosh, I'm so jealous.

78
00:04:11,060 --> 00:04:13,420
You have a son
who can drink with you.

79
00:04:17,260 --> 00:04:19,300
Mr. Choi has terminal cancer.

80
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:20,900
That's why it turned out this way.

81
00:04:23,370 --> 00:04:25,040
I see.

82
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:26,600
His son is quite young.

83
00:04:26,670 --> 00:04:28,740
So he probably thinks differently
from his father.

84
00:04:29,410 --> 00:04:32,740
He was acting all condescending,
so I taught him a lesson.

85
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:35,980
I see.

86
00:04:36,180 --> 00:04:39,050
I'm meeting with people
in the industry now.

87
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:40,920
I believe I'll get a job soon.

88
00:04:41,150 --> 00:04:44,020
I was going to tell you
the whole thing after that.

89
00:04:45,290 --> 00:04:46,290
Okay.

90
00:04:46,690 --> 00:04:48,760
Do Ji Wan and Su Bin know too?

91
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:51,100
Not yet.

92
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,330
I think you should tell them
as soon as possible.

93
00:04:53,770 --> 00:04:55,300
No.
I'll tell them after I get a job.

94
00:04:55,770 --> 00:04:57,940
I don't want to disappoint them.

95
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,810
We don't know when it will be.

96
00:05:02,170 --> 00:05:03,170
What?

97
00:05:03,340 --> 00:05:06,180
Finding a new job
after retirement isn't so easy.

98
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:08,010
Pull yourself together.

99
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:11,880
That's what happens
after you retire.

100
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:13,950
That's reality.

101
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,550
Right.

102
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:18,290
It's not easy. It will be hard.

103
00:05:19,490 --> 00:05:21,560
It's not like I don't know that.

104
00:05:21,890 --> 00:05:24,330
I have a lot of colleagues...

105
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:26,160
who left the company before me...

106
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:29,030
and are now struggling
with harsh realities.

107
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:31,500
Still, I was hired
by another company...

108
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:33,570
even before my retirement.

109
00:05:33,770 --> 00:05:36,070
There must be a reason for that.

110
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:38,880
I'll tell Ji Wan and Su Bin
about this.

111
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,380
Mom and Grandma
will have a hard time...

112
00:05:41,380 --> 00:05:42,650
pretending everything's fine.

113
00:05:42,650 --> 00:05:43,850
Don't say anything.

114
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:46,820
Don't tell Ji Wan and Su Bin.

115
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:48,850
And don't show it
to your mom and grandma.

116
00:05:49,150 --> 00:05:50,990
It's not the kind of thing
that should be kept secret.

117
00:05:51,090 --> 00:05:52,960
It's something
that happens to everyone.

118
00:05:53,390 --> 00:05:54,930
Try as we might,
but we're just employees.

119
00:05:55,790 --> 00:06:00,000
Don't be so quick to assume
that your dad will end up like that.

120
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:03,740
It's not like we have to worry
about living expenses now.

121
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:05,440
You have your job.

122
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,640
And Ji Wan doesn't need my support.

123
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:10,240
I just need to support Su Bin.
What's there to worry about?

124
00:06:10,340 --> 00:06:12,440
I'm telling you
it'll take 2 to 3 months at most.

125
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,920
Where are you planning to work?

126
00:06:21,950 --> 00:06:23,550
Of course,
it's the textile industry.

127
00:06:23,620 --> 00:06:25,220
It doesn't have to be
the same industry.

128
00:06:25,220 --> 00:06:26,360
Keep your options open.

129
00:06:26,390 --> 00:06:29,430
Come on.
I'll take care of it myself.

130
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,530
Where do you spend your time
outside?

131
00:06:32,530 --> 00:06:33,970
Where do you think?

132
00:06:34,070 --> 00:06:36,170
I'm busy meeting people
in the industry...

133
00:06:36,170 --> 00:06:37,640
and asking for a job.

134
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,840
I go hiking sometimes.

135
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,240
I also go for a game of pool
here and there.

136
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:42,940
I meet my friends from college too.

137
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:47,650
- Here.
- Okay.

138
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:52,850
Oh, dear.

139
00:06:52,850 --> 00:06:55,420
How long has it been since
we last walked together like this?

140
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,320
It's been a long time.

141
00:07:00,890 --> 00:07:01,890
Hey.

142
00:07:02,330 --> 00:07:05,230
By the way,
why am I looking up at you now?

143
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:09,030
It feels like just yesterday
I was looking down at you.

144
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:11,470
That was a long time ago.

145
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:14,940
It's been a million years
since I got taller than you.

146
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:17,210
Really?

147
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,580
Fine. You're tall.

148
00:07:22,450 --> 00:07:24,350
Of course. I'm your son, aren't I?

149
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,550
(Jung Hyeon Su Architecture Lab)

150
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:30,150
Do you mind if I leave now?

151
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:31,660
I need to run.

152
00:07:41,170 --> 00:07:42,830
If you can't hide how upset you are,

153
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,570
you'd be better off
quitting the cafe.

154
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:05,720
Fine, Lee Ji Hyuk.
I will forget everything.

155
00:08:06,290 --> 00:08:08,630
I'll end things completely.

156
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:16,330
I've thought all about it.

157
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:17,940
Do you think
I haven't thought about it?

158
00:08:18,570 --> 00:08:20,570
Why don't I deserve to be with you?

159
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:23,940
Because I'm not feminine?
Because I don't dress myself up?

160
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:26,510
Because I have a bad personality
or a strong personality?

161
00:08:26,940 --> 00:08:28,210
Because we have different tastes?

162
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:30,110
That wasn't the case.

163
00:08:31,220 --> 00:08:32,450
Then the only reason remaining is...

164
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:34,420
Because of my background?

165
00:08:35,290 --> 00:08:36,750
Because I'm from a poor family?

166
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:39,960
Because I don't make good money?

167
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:42,960
That can't be the reason.

168
00:08:43,330 --> 00:08:44,860
You don't want to get married.

169
00:08:45,530 --> 00:08:47,060
You have no reason
to care about my background...

170
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:48,900
when you have no intention
of getting married.

171
00:08:50,870 --> 00:08:52,040
What on earth is it?

172
00:08:53,070 --> 00:08:54,940
I don't know
why you are not telling me.

173
00:09:02,110 --> 00:09:03,880
(Buy 8 cans of beer
and get 3 dollars cash back.)

174
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,680
No.

175
00:09:07,590 --> 00:09:09,220
I won't drown my sorrows in drink.

176
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:11,490
I can get over it myself.

177
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:21,900
Oh, dear.

178
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,470
We have ginseng wine
left over from the ancestral rite.

179
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:55,690
I saw Gang Oh
make highballs in secret.

180
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:20,890
I feel so weird.

181
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:22,390
My leg hurts.

182
00:11:24,660 --> 00:11:26,220
This is killing me.

183
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:29,030
Isn't that your sister?

184
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:30,430
- I think it is.
- Oh, no.

185
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,230
What...

186
00:11:33,230 --> 00:11:34,400
Eun Oh.

187
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:36,230
My gosh.

188
00:11:39,140 --> 00:11:40,440
- Eun Oh.
- Ji Eun Oh.

189
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,910
My goodness. Eun Oh!

190
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:46,280
Da Jeong.

191
00:11:46,510 --> 00:11:47,750
When people say,

192
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:49,580
"The elderly are welcome,"

193
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:52,520
what age range do they mean?

194
00:11:53,420 --> 00:11:54,990
Where are they welcome?

195
00:11:55,420 --> 00:11:57,560
I was walking by...

196
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:59,090
a restaurant or something,

197
00:11:59,420 --> 00:12:01,430
and they were looking for help.

198
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:05,030
Wouldn't they mean 65 years old?

199
00:12:05,330 --> 00:12:07,730
People aged 65 and over
can use public transport for free.

200
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:11,740
Sixty-five?

201
00:12:14,370 --> 00:12:16,810
They're babies compared to you,

202
00:12:16,810 --> 00:12:18,080
if they're 65.

203
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:39,330
(Library Village)

204
00:12:57,450 --> 00:12:59,850
How much did she drink
and how hungover is she...

205
00:12:59,850 --> 00:13:01,090
that you called a part-timer?

206
00:13:01,890 --> 00:13:04,120
She was at the ER all night.

207
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:07,190
She passed out after drinking...

208
00:13:07,190 --> 00:13:09,390
way too many
different kinds of liquor,

209
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:11,060
and they pumped her stomach
thinking she'd overdosed.

210
00:13:14,330 --> 00:13:16,600
On top of that,
she's overworked and fatigued,

211
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,500
so she needs to take
a week or so off.

212
00:13:27,950 --> 00:13:29,680
(Park Seong Jae)

213
00:13:35,020 --> 00:13:37,860
Ji Hyuk.
I think Eun Oh is really sick.

214
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,760
She went to the ER.

215
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:54,170
(Incoming call: Park Seong Jae)

216
00:13:58,710 --> 00:13:59,710
So what?

217
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,250
What?

218
00:14:01,250 --> 00:14:02,580
I got the text about Eun Oh.

219
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:04,280
Where is she now?

220
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,520
She's resting at home.

221
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:10,590
She's fine, then.

222
00:14:11,390 --> 00:14:12,390
Bye.

223
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:13,520
Hey.

224
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:27,040
Yes, sir.

225
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:29,070
Call Yurim Korean Medicine Clinic,
please.

226
00:14:55,630 --> 00:14:57,070
(Apple mangoes)

227
00:15:05,610 --> 00:15:06,680
Goodness.

228
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:08,150
Eun Oh.

229
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:12,620
Someone sent you
some expensive gongjindan.

230
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:13,820
My gosh.

231
00:15:13,820 --> 00:15:15,520
There's fruit and tea as well,

232
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:18,260
not to mention various snacks.

233
00:15:18,890 --> 00:15:19,890
Hang on.

234
00:15:21,430 --> 00:15:22,690
"Park Seong Jae."

235
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:24,760
Who's this?

236
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:27,430
(Get well soon.
From Park Seong Jae.)

237
00:15:27,430 --> 00:15:28,870
Get well soon.

238
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:30,900
A cafe regular.

239
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,140
What?

240
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:34,970
You never run out of things to eat.

241
00:15:34,970 --> 00:15:36,570
Someone sent bread
from a new bakery.

242
00:15:36,570 --> 00:15:37,780
They must know you well.

243
00:15:39,140 --> 00:15:40,380
You can have it.

244
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,850
- What?
- For real? Thank you.

245
00:15:41,850 --> 00:15:43,450
Don't touch it.

246
00:15:43,450 --> 00:15:44,850
Let her pick first.
You can eat later.

247
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:49,220
Eun Oh. You had some porridge.

248
00:15:49,220 --> 00:15:52,060
Pick out what bread you want
and eat it when you feel like it.

249
00:15:52,060 --> 00:15:53,820
Take a bite at least.

250
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:56,530
- Sit up.
- My gosh.

251
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:59,200
Here.

252
00:16:00,730 --> 00:16:02,500
Pick something out.

253
00:16:07,140 --> 00:16:08,210
My goodness.

254
00:16:10,410 --> 00:16:12,840
They have bread
shaped like a coal briquette?

255
00:16:14,180 --> 00:16:15,780
They're serious about marketing.

256
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,820
- Look at what they wrote.
- What?

257
00:16:17,820 --> 00:16:19,850
"We hope the sweet aroma..."

258
00:16:19,850 --> 00:16:21,390
"is deeply comforting."

259
00:16:22,420 --> 00:16:23,690
I'm getting goosebumps.

260
00:16:30,060 --> 00:16:31,200
You can take those.

261
00:16:33,430 --> 00:16:35,670
Oh, dear. Lie down and rest.

262
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:41,310
Do you have a fever?

263
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:53,720
Mr. Lee.

264
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,890
My knees hurt so bad.

265
00:16:57,190 --> 00:17:00,320
Your feet are almost parallel.

266
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:03,560
Stand so your toes face outward.

267
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:05,900
Keep them shoulder-width apart,

268
