00:34:16,890 --> 00:34:19,700
that you lost your shoes
several times.

539
00:34:20,030 --> 00:34:21,060
I'll keep it a secret.

540
00:34:23,870 --> 00:34:25,270
Here. Put these on.

541
00:34:26,470 --> 00:34:27,840
- You brat.
- No.

542
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:28,910
No.

543
00:34:28,910 --> 00:34:31,240
What do you mean, no? You little...

544
00:34:31,240 --> 00:34:33,280
Hey. Let him up.

545
00:34:35,310 --> 00:34:36,310
Darn it.

546
00:34:39,550 --> 00:34:40,580
Park Seong Jae.

547
00:34:41,020 --> 00:34:42,190
Take off your shoes.

548
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:44,520
Hey!

549
00:34:47,990 --> 00:34:49,060
That's enough.

550
00:34:49,460 --> 00:34:50,830
You let him run errands
every morning,

551
00:34:50,830 --> 00:34:51,960
steal his shoes,

552
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:54,230
and even take money from him
every Monday. Isn't that enough?

553
00:34:56,070 --> 00:34:57,070
Look at you.

554
00:34:57,570 --> 00:34:59,170
Lee Ji Hyuk, you nerd.

555
00:34:59,170 --> 00:35:00,740
You're not watching your mouth
because you get good grades?

556
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:04,110
He's in my class,
and I'm the class president.

557
00:35:04,110 --> 00:35:06,510
So what? You are the class president
only at school.

558
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:08,850
Are you the president
of the neighborhood or what?

559
00:35:09,410 --> 00:35:10,750
Hey.

560
00:35:12,650 --> 00:35:14,820
- Trample on him.
- You are so cool, Go Dae Yong.

561
00:35:15,950 --> 00:35:16,990
Why?

562
00:35:18,650 --> 00:35:20,090
Can't you beat me on your own?

563
00:35:23,260 --> 00:35:24,260
What?

564
00:35:25,730 --> 00:35:27,200
If you want to fight,
do it man-to-man.

565
00:35:27,830 --> 00:35:29,430
You pathetic coward, Go Dae Yong.

566
00:35:30,070 --> 00:35:31,670
You can't deal with me
on your own, can you?

567
00:35:31,670 --> 00:35:32,800
Lee Ji Hyuk, you...

568
00:35:33,670 --> 00:35:34,870
Is something wrong
with your brain today?

569
00:35:34,870 --> 00:35:35,970
Just answer me.

570
00:35:36,710 --> 00:35:37,710
Let's fight one-on-one.

571
00:35:39,440 --> 00:35:41,710
Lee Ji Hyuk, don't regret it
even if you die today.

572
00:35:41,710 --> 00:35:42,750
I'll smash you to bits.

573
00:35:42,750 --> 00:35:44,180
If you lose to me,

574
00:35:44,180 --> 00:35:45,720
don't mess with Park Seong Jae
ever again.

575
00:35:45,720 --> 00:35:47,250
- Hey.
- Go easy on him.

576
00:35:47,250 --> 00:35:49,190
- Cool.
- Nice.

577
00:36:00,430 --> 00:36:01,430
Hey.

578
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:14,110
What? Stop it already!

579
00:36:27,260 --> 00:36:29,830
Let go. Get off me.

580
00:36:29,830 --> 00:36:30,830
Hey.

581
00:36:34,230 --> 00:36:35,870
Hey, Go Dae Yong!

582
00:36:35,870 --> 00:36:38,570
Hey! Wake up.

583
00:36:38,570 --> 00:36:40,000
- Darn it.
- Hey.

584
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,800
He's no big deal. Let's go.

585
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:43,710
- Hey, wake up.
- What's wrong with him?

586
00:36:46,410 --> 00:36:47,680
Did you all see that?

587
00:36:49,610 --> 00:36:51,380
You can't mess
with Park Seong Jae anymore.

588
00:36:53,420 --> 00:36:54,680
Shut it.

589
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:56,050
It's not like you got hit.

590
00:36:57,820 --> 00:36:58,890
Darn it.

591
00:37:05,460 --> 00:37:07,800
He was a good person back then too.

592
00:37:09,970 --> 00:37:12,870
But why did you let them
bully you like that?

593
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,040
Were you too scared?

594
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:20,080
I guess I was.

595
00:37:24,980 --> 00:37:26,320
I should get going.

596
00:37:53,710 --> 00:37:54,910
(Park Seong Jae)

597
00:37:54,910 --> 00:37:56,380
Let me ease your worries.

598
00:37:56,610 --> 00:37:58,050
Eun Oh came to work today.

599
00:37:59,180 --> 00:38:00,220
You rascal.

600
00:38:02,250 --> 00:38:03,320
That's a relief.

601
00:38:09,730 --> 00:38:10,760
(Congratulations on your opening.
From Eunoism Design)

602
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:12,460
You didn't have to bring this.

603
00:38:12,460 --> 00:38:13,830
Congratulations.

604
00:38:13,830 --> 00:38:15,460
Thank you.

605
00:38:16,670 --> 00:38:18,930
This space is crazy.

606
00:38:18,930 --> 00:38:20,540
- Really?
- People are posting...

607
00:38:20,540 --> 00:38:22,240
photos of this on social media.

608
00:38:46,100 --> 00:38:47,160
I thought...

609
00:38:48,100 --> 00:38:49,770
the wheel seemed familiar.

610
00:38:50,970 --> 00:38:52,030
I heard you were sick.

611
00:38:53,540 --> 00:38:54,900
I knew you'd be like that.

612
00:38:55,440 --> 00:38:56,640
You shouldn't skip meals.

613
00:38:57,710 --> 00:38:58,810
You're annoying.

614
00:38:59,710 --> 00:39:00,980
I guess I am.

615
00:39:02,710 --> 00:39:03,810
Are you feeling better?

616
00:39:04,780 --> 00:39:06,520
After getting some good rest,

617
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:08,050
I feel even better
than before I got sick.

618
00:39:09,850 --> 00:39:10,950
Where have you been?

619
00:39:11,790 --> 00:39:13,460
The cafe I renovated is open.

620
00:39:13,460 --> 00:39:15,090
I went there to deliver a gift...

621
00:39:15,090 --> 00:39:16,660
and check on any issues.

622
00:39:17,430 --> 00:39:18,490
When does the next project begin?

623
00:39:19,260 --> 00:39:20,260
I don't have any plans yet.

624
00:39:30,710 --> 00:39:33,240
By the way, I got an email
from our university juniors.

625
00:39:33,940 --> 00:39:36,450
They came up with 30 ideas...

626
00:39:36,450 --> 00:39:38,510
because it's our 30th anniversary.

627
00:39:38,750 --> 00:39:41,650
Are they going to skip
lectures and exams...

628
00:39:41,780 --> 00:39:42,890
and spend...

629
00:39:42,890 --> 00:39:45,090
the whole semester doing club stuff?

630
00:39:45,390 --> 00:39:46,720
It's just a club, not a calling.

631
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:49,460
That's exactly what you were like.

632
00:39:50,290 --> 00:39:52,960
That was because
I was thinking of...

633
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:54,860
becoming an interior designer.

634
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:57,230
They want to redo two places
this time...

635
00:39:57,330 --> 00:39:59,070
during the whole summer vacation.

636
00:39:59,740 --> 00:40:02,000
I don't mind
drawing the floor plans,

637
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:04,870
but we'll need to blackmail
the technical majors, right?

638
00:40:07,410 --> 00:40:08,410
Eun Oh.

639
00:40:15,990 --> 00:40:17,090
Don't try too hard.

640
00:40:18,390 --> 00:40:20,260
- What?
- To keep talking.

641
00:40:21,620 --> 00:40:22,660
You don't have to.

642
00:40:24,860 --> 00:40:27,530
I always talked a bit too much
whenever...

643
00:40:27,530 --> 00:40:28,830
we were going somewhere.

644
00:40:29,030 --> 00:40:30,230
Not this much, though.

645
00:40:31,070 --> 00:40:32,200
You took time to breathe.

646
00:40:33,940 --> 00:40:34,970
Did I?

647
00:40:35,870 --> 00:40:39,440
You can be so mean sometimes.

648
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:40,810
You're too honest.

649
00:40:42,010 --> 00:40:43,080
Not all the time.

650
00:40:44,780 --> 00:40:46,480
I'm mostly honest.

651
00:40:47,720 --> 00:40:51,050
But sometimes,
I pretend to be honest.

652
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:55,560
When you do pretend to be honest?

653
00:40:57,090 --> 00:40:59,500
When I need to.
When I feel uncomfortable.

654
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:02,900
When I'm a coward.

655
00:41:04,870 --> 00:41:07,000
You're like that too.

656
00:41:09,410 --> 00:41:10,640
We're all human.

657
00:41:11,570 --> 00:41:13,540
Do you think some are different?

658
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:14,980
You fool.

659
00:41:29,990 --> 00:41:31,030
Go on inside.

660
00:41:32,630 --> 00:41:34,230
You're not coming to the cafe?

661
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:37,330
Seong Jae told me
you were back at work.

662
00:41:37,500 --> 00:41:38,630
I dropped by to see you.

663
00:41:39,570 --> 00:41:40,570
I see.

664
00:41:44,610 --> 00:41:46,010
The next guy you choose...

665
00:41:47,910 --> 00:41:50,050
should be kind,
not simply someone you like.

666
00:41:51,810 --> 00:41:53,150
Liking someone is about feelings,

667
00:41:53,780 --> 00:41:54,820
and feelings...

668
00:41:57,690 --> 00:41:58,750
are powerless.

669
00:42:07,030 --> 00:42:09,870
That's some cool-sounding advice.

670
00:42:12,900 --> 00:42:15,200
Eat regularly. You've lost weight.

671
00:42:18,010 --> 00:42:19,040
Okay.

672
00:42:20,140 --> 00:42:22,280
Take care, Ji Hyuk.

673
00:43:04,950 --> 00:43:05,960
Would you like to order?

674
00:43:06,860 --> 00:43:08,020
Not exactly.

675
00:43:08,190 --> 00:43:10,860
Is this your design portfolio?

676
00:43:10,860 --> 00:43:12,390
No, it's not mine.

677
00:43:12,660 --> 00:43:14,860
Here she is. It's hers.

678
00:43:16,270 --> 00:43:17,270
Aren't you...

679
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:20,700
Are you...

680
00:43:21,640 --> 00:43:24,540
Hello. Do you feel better?

681
00:43:25,340 --> 00:43:27,080
It really is you
from the subway station.

682
00:43:27,680 --> 00:43:29,180
I'm fine, thanks to you.

683
00:43:29,910 --> 00:43:31,110
That's good to hear.

684
00:43:31,180 --> 00:43:33,050
Eun Oh. Do you know her?

685
00:43:33,520 --> 00:43:35,820
- Well...
- I was curious about this designer.

686
00:43:36,020 --> 00:43:37,450
It was you.

687
00:43:37,590 --> 00:43:39,390
Well, yes.

688
00:43:39,760 --> 00:43:43,960
If you don't mind,
could we perhaps talk for a bit?

689
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:46,160
Well...

690
00:43:46,630 --> 00:43:47,660
It's quiet right now.

691
00:43:48,700 --> 00:43:50,330
I can spare a few minutes.

692
00:44:02,010 --> 00:44:04,410
I didn't know you had company.

693
00:44:05,010 --> 00:44:06,120
Our business was done.

694
00:44:11,820 --> 00:44:13,120
I accepted it...

695
00:44:13,360 --> 00:44:15,720
and gave up on him. I'll try...

696
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:18,430
to go back
to how things were before.

697
00:44:19,930 --> 00:44:21,830
You care about Eun Oh so much.

698
00:44:22,060 --> 00:44:24,300
Why did you make her ask me out
and get hurt?

699
00:44:25,200 --> 00:44:27,200
Whenever I tried to approach Eun Oh,

700
00:44:27,200 --> 00:44:29,100
you tried to stop me.

701
00:44:29,770 --> 00:44:30,940
You said I couldn't be with her.

702
00:44:31,970 --> 00:44:33,510
That I didn't deserve her.

703
00:44:34,480 --> 00:44:35,540
You said...

704
00:44:36,980 --> 00:44:38,110
I didn't deserve her.

705
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:42,990
You don't need to follow me in,

706
00:44:43,190 --> 00:44:44,250
and I don't need tea.

707
00:44:44,820 --> 00:44:46,260
It's a sudden raid.

708
00:44:47,720 --> 00:44:50,860
There's talk that you go out
for 30 minutes to an hour.

709
00:44:54,260 --> 00:44:56,270
This is inappropriate as a father...

710
00:44:56,870 --> 00:44:58,200
and as a superior.

711
00:44:58,470 --> 00:45:00,000
I'm here for two reasons.

712
00:45:01,070 --> 00:45:04,270
"I'm going to marry the person
I naturally end up dating."

713
00:45:04,510 --> 00:45:06,410
"If I marry, that is."

714
00:45:06,640 --> 00:45:07,880
It's pretty vague.

715
00:45:08,480 --> 00:45:11,350
Tell me clearly
if you intend to marry or not.

716
00:45:12,580 --> 00:45:14,480
Are you slacking off
because sales went up?

717
00:45:16,850 --> 00:45:18,890
Did you make me a director
without allowing me...

718
00:45:19,290 --> 00:45:20,690
to manage my own schedule?

719
00:45:21,060 --> 00:45:22,260
And about marriage.

720
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:23,990
It's as I said.

721
00:45:24,490 --> 00:45:25,990
You have until the end of the year.

722
00:45:26,200 --> 00:45:28,060
If you don't find someone
until then,

723
00:45:28,300 --> 00:45:29,870
that's a shortcoming on your part.

724
00:45:30,830 --> 00:45:34,570
I expect you to marry
the woman I find you.

725
00:45:39,440 --> 00:45:41,040
(Shoealls)

726
00:45:46,420 --> 00:45:48,750
I'm preparing a project, you see.

727
00:45:49,320 --> 00:45:52,490
I was looking for someone
to design the interior,

728
00:45:52,750 --> 00:45:53,990
and I happened to...

729
00:45:54,220 --> 00:45:56,630
Sorry. What's your name?

730
00:45:57,360 --> 00:45:59,660
Oh, my name is Ji Eun Oh.

731
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:01,630
I see.

732
00:46:01,930 --> 00:46:06,100
That's why the company's called
Eunoism Design.

733
00:46:06,100 --> 00:46:07,140
Yes.

734
00:46:11,440 --> 00:46:13,040
My name is Ko Seong Hui.

735
00:46:13,040 --> 00:46:14,240
(Gaon Foundation, Ko Seong Hui)

736
00:46:14,580 --> 00:46:16,680
I guess you could call it
a space for art and design.

737
00:46:17,250 --> 00:46:19,480
I was planning something like that.

738
00:46:19,780 --> 00:46:22,220
I happened to see your portfolio,

739
00:46:22,220 --> 00:46:23,590
and I quite liked it.

740
00:46:25,220 --> 00:46:26,960
Oh, I see.

741
00:46:27,960 --> 00:46:29,730
I'd like to give you the job.

742
00:46:29,990 --> 00:46:31,590
You don't seem to have
much experience.

743
00:46:32,390 --> 00:46:36,270
No. I got into interior design
about a year ago.

744
00:46:36,530 --> 00:46:39,430
Then three businesses and this cafe.

745
00:46:39,430 --> 00:46:41,040
- You designed four spaces?
- Yes.

746
00:46:41,370 --> 00:46:43,440
I did the interior
of a few studio apartments,

747
00:46:43,510 --> 00:46:45,870
but those were friends' places
I did for free for the experience.

748
00:46:48,010 --> 00:46:51,810
I don't know how big
the project you're planning is,

749
00:46:52,250 --> 00:46:54,950
but you should look into others
with more experience too.

750
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:57,720
If you tell me the image you want,

751
00:46:57,720 --> 00:46:59,720
I'll sketch something
for you to look at.

752
00:46:59,720 --> 00:47:01,190
You can decide then.

753
00:47:01,590 --> 00:47:03,890
You can even decide
after I give you an estimate.

754
00:47:05,390 --> 00:47:07,130
Why would you say that?

755
00:47:08,030 --> 00:47:10,630
- Pardon?
- I like you, and that's it.

756
00:47:12,730 --> 00:47:14,000
I want you to do it.

757
00:47:15,770 --> 00:47:17,040
Me?

758
00:47:18,140 --> 00:47:20,380
I got the feel
when I saw your portfolio.

759
00:47:22,380 --> 00:47:25,050
I have another appointment.

760
00:47:25,650 --> 00:47:27,620
I'd like to discuss
the details in person.

761
00:47:27,820 --> 00:47:29,080
When are you free?

762
00:47:29,520 --> 00:47:31,320
I'm free whenever you are.

763
00:47:32,550 --> 00:47:33,720
What about this cafe?

764
00:47:34,620 --> 00:47:37,590
I accepted the manager role
because I'm allowed to come and go.

765
00:47:38,030 --> 00:47:40,400
A senior of my university club
invested in the cafe.

766
00:47:40,830 --> 00:47:43,500
I thought it was a nice place.

767
00:47:43,630 --> 00:47:45,770
It's where cool people gather.

768
00:47:48,700 --> 00:47:50,170
My number's on that card.

769
00:47:50,740 --> 00:47:52,310
Text me your number.

770
00:47:53,310 --> 00:47:54,780
Okay. I'll do that.

771
00:47:55,640 --> 00:47:57,310
I hope to see you soon.

772
00:47:58,650 --> 00:47:59,720
Yes.

773
00:48:02,750 --> 00:48:05,150
(Gaon Foundation, Ko Seong Hui)

774
00:48:05,490 --> 00:48:07,020
This is insane.

775
00:48:07,060 --> 00:48:10,230
It must be true
that deities bless good people.

776
00:48:10,730 --> 00:48:12,060
It's not official yet.

777
00:48:12,390 --> 00:48:14,860
She could've given me the job
impulsively...

778
00:48:14,860 --> 00:48:16,830
because I'd helped her.

779
00:48:18,530 --> 00:48:20,270
I really hope she calls.

780
00:48:20,640 --> 00:48:21,700
Me too.

781
00:48:21,700 --> 00:48:23,540
I need something to concentrate on.

782
00:48:23,970 --> 00:48:26,710
I gave an estimate for an apartment,
but the person didn't call.

783
00:48:53,640 --> 00:48:55,870
You should place it there.

784
00:49:30,170 --> 00:49:32,240
(6 a.m., Alarm)

785
00:49:35,680 --> 00:49:37,550
Who's calling this early?

786
00:49:38,680 --> 00:49:41,250
Dad's job offer at Seongil Weaving
was canceled.

787
00:49:43,690 --> 00:49:45,450
He hasn't been able to tell us...

788
00:49:45,890 --> 00:49:47,960
and goes out each day
searching for a job.

789
00:49:51,190 --> 00:49:52,290
Shoot.

790
00:49:54,430 --> 00:49:55,500
Pull yourself together.

791
00:49:56,060 --> 00:49:57,300
You can't afford to sleep in.

792
00:49:58,130 --> 00:49:59,870
The family can't know
you were fired.

793
00:50:34,370 --> 00:50:36,870
I'll catch this punk
the second I see him.

794
00:50:36,870 --> 00:50:38,240
So don't worry, and head inside.

795
00:50:40,180 --> 00:50:41,180
Right.

796
00:50:41,710 --> 00:50:42,840
Thank you.

797
00:51:36,730 --> 00:51:38,070
It's been a while, Yeong Ra.

798
00:51:38,730 --> 00:51:40,100
You know how I feel about you now.

799
00:51:51,650 --> 00:51:53,150
- Let go!
- Yeong Ra!

800
00:51:53,150 --> 00:51:54,750
- No...
- Yeong Ra, wait.

801
00:51:57,150 --> 00:51:58,520
Come on, Yeong Ra.

802
00:51:59,420 --> 00:52:02,060
Haven't I done enough
to prove how I feel?

803
00:52:03,160 --> 00:52:05,090
I gave you a flower like this
at your graduation exhibition.

804
00:52:05,090 --> 00:52:06,160
Don't you remember that?

805
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:08,330
No...

806
00:52:11,300 --> 00:52:12,400
I'm not a scary person.

807
00:52:12,400 --> 00:52:14,400
- Please don't hurt me.
- Yeong Ra.

808
00:52:14,400 --> 00:52:16,540
Please don't hurt me. Please.

809
00:52:16,540 --> 00:52:17,710
What's going on?

810
00:52:19,270 --> 00:52:20,340
Who are you?

811
00:52:27,050 --> 00:52:28,150
Ms. Park.

812
00:52:28,750 --> 00:52:29,950
Who was that man?

813
00:52:30,220 --> 00:52:31,390
Should I call the police?

814
00:52:31,750 --> 00:52:34,320
You can't get caught up
in any kind of scandal.

815
00:52:34,560 --> 00:52:37,190
No, please don't.

816
00:52:37,990 --> 00:52:40,130
He's probably a fan,

817
00:52:40,530 --> 00:52:42,660
and I was just startled
that he suddenly came by.

818
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:44,970
A fan who shows up
out of the blue like that...

819
00:52:44,970 --> 00:52:46,330
is most likely a stalker.

820
00:52:46,330 --> 00:52:48,140
No, it's not that.

821
00:52:50,410 --> 00:52:51,740
I'm fine, Jeong Hui.

822
00:53:01,850 --> 00:53:02,950
I'll be fine.

823
00:53:20,870 --> 00:53:22,600
How long are you going
to think this through?

824
00:53:24,510 --> 00:53:25,810
What will it be?

825
00:53:27,510 --> 00:53:28,640
What are you going to do?

826
00:53:41,060 --> 00:53:42,560
This is Ruche General Contractor.

827
00:53:42,720 --> 00:53:44,360
We were impressed by your resume...

828
00:53:44,730 --> 00:53:46,930
and will contact you next week
to schedule an interview.

829
00:53:52,500 --> 00:53:53,840
Way to go.

830
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:57,570
Didn't you quit tennis
over three years ago?

831
00:53:58,940 --> 00:54:00,240
What are you even doing here?

832
00:54:00,240 --> 00:54:01,440
How did you know I was here?

833
00:54:01,440 --> 00:54:03,610
I tracked your GPS. Happy now?

834
00:54:03,810 --> 00:54:04,850
What's gotten into you?

835
00:54:17,330 --> 00:54:19,490
Eun Oh, it's about Ji Hyuk.

836
00:54:19,490 --> 00:54:21,100
Stop. Don't mention his name.

837
00:54:21,760 --> 00:54:24,100
Isn't it strange
that he hasn't been at the cafe...

838
00:54:24,100 --> 00:54:26,870
and hasn't even contacted Mr. Park?

839
00:54:27,640 --> 00:54:29,940
It's odd. Very odd.

840
00:54:30,610 --> 00:54:32,370
But since I need to move on
with my life,

841
00:54:32,370 --> 00:54:33,440
I won't think about it.

842
00:54:35,240 --> 00:54:38,310
Got it. I won't mention
Lee Ji Hyuk from now on.

843
00:54:41,280 --> 00:54:42,850
You've been ignoring
my texts and calls,

844
00:54:43,250 --> 00:54:44,950
and you still refuse
to talk to me in person.

845
00:54:45,720 --> 00:54:47,620
Am I even still a friend to you?

846
00:54:47,620 --> 00:54:49,460
I texted saying
I wanted to be alone.

847
00:54:50,090 --> 00:54:52,190
Why did you come find me
instead of just letting me be?

848
00:54:52,890 --> 00:54:54,600
I searched for you
at the pool you go to,

849
00:54:54,600 --> 00:54:56,670
at the Han River,
and at the free diving pool,

850
00:54:58,070 --> 00:54:59,600
and then came here just in case.

851
00:55:01,870 --> 00:55:04,240
Why? Is something up?

852
00:55:04,340 --> 00:55:05,340
What is it?

853
00:55:05,340 --> 00:55:07,810
As if something would be up
with someone as boring as me.

854
00:55:08,880 --> 00:55:10,280
I looked for you to give you this.

855
00:55:12,050 --> 00:55:13,080
What's this?

856
00:55:13,780 --> 00:55:15,550
This is the guest studio apartment
owned by our company.

857
00:55:16,420 --> 00:55:18,620
You've probably been
wandering around...

858
00:55:18,620 --> 00:55:20,460
after leaving home
saying you were headed to work.

859
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:22,160
Spend your time there instead.

860
00:55:28,300 --> 00:55:29,830
You're being generous...

861
00:55:29,830 --> 00:55:31,470
despite not knowing
the situation I'm in.

862
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:34,140
You...

863
00:55:35,270 --> 00:55:37,270
Don't waste your time
at places like this.

864
00:55:37,270 --> 00:55:38,340
It's pathetic.

865
00:55:38,970 --> 00:55:40,040
What's so pathetic?

866
00:55:40,710 --> 00:55:43,040
Playing sports is the best way
to clear your head and think.

867
00:55:43,750 --> 00:55:45,880
Head to the unit starting tomorrow
and look for jobs.

868
00:55:45,880 --> 00:55:47,520
You still haven't decided on one,
have you?

869
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:49,880
A job?

870
00:55:50,490 --> 00:55:53,620
Doesn't your line of work
hire people with experience?

871
00:55:56,390 --> 00:55:57,390
(Libeore)

872
00:55:57,460 --> 00:55:59,790
It's not my work but another matter
I had to think about.

873
00:56:00,060 --> 00:56:01,060
As in what?

874
00:56:01,400 --> 00:56:03,060
Is something else up
with the family?

875
00:56:04,800 --> 00:56:07,070
I was thinking about
how it would be...

876
00:56:07,640 --> 00:56:08,770
to marry Jung Bo A.

877
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:11,070
Jung Bo A?

878
00:56:12,470 --> 00:56:13,480
Hold on.

879
00:56:13,880 --> 00:56:15,580
Jung Bo A at Haneul Construction?

880
00:56:16,680 --> 00:56:17,680
Yes.

881
00:56:18,550 --> 00:56:20,120
She asked me to marry her,

882
00:56:20,750 --> 00:56:21,750
and that's what I was considering.

883
00:56:22,280 --> 00:56:23,350
Quite seriously, too.

884
00:56:23,520 --> 00:56:24,720
She asked you to marry her?

885
00:56:25,290 --> 00:56:26,990
Jung Bo A asked you to marry her?

886
00:56:27,860 --> 00:56:28,860
Yes.

887
00:56:28,890 --> 00:56:29,890
Why?

888
00:56:31,290 --> 00:56:33,290
Because she wants to marry me.

889
00:56:33,800 --> 00:56:34,800
Did she really ask you?

890
00:56:35,230 --> 00:56:36,300
She did.

891
00:56:42,140 --> 00:56:44,840
I couldn't care less
about her state of mind,

892
00:56:46,610 --> 00:56:48,640
but you don't seem
to be joking about this.

893
00:56:49,380 --> 00:56:51,280
But how is this even up for debate?

894
00:56:52,480 --> 00:56:53,780
Can't I consider it?

895
00:56:54,620 --> 00:56:56,580
There's nothing
between you and Jung Bo A.

896
00:56:58,620 --> 00:56:59,690
How can you be sure...

897
00:57:00,050 --> 00:57:01,660
that there's nothing between us?

898
00:57:01,660 --> 00:57:02,820
I'm sure.

899
00:57:02,820 --> 00:57:04,290
You don't love her,

900
00:57:04,290 --> 00:57:06,330
and she doesn't love you either.
Am I wrong?

901
00:57:08,230 --> 00:57:09,230
Love?

902
00:57:11,070 --> 00:57:12,400
Sure. We're not in love.

903
00:57:12,800 --> 00:57:14,070
Exactly.

904
00:57:14,340 --> 00:57:16,400
So what the heck am I even hearing?

905
00:57:16,500 --> 00:57:19,010
Why did she propose
something so ridiculous,

906
00:57:19,010 --> 00:57:20,210
and why are you...

907
00:57:20,680 --> 00:57:22,310
even considering it?

908
00:57:23,610 --> 00:57:24,880
Is this a comedy sitcom?

909
00:57:25,280 --> 00:57:27,750
Lee Ji Hyuk, what's gotten into you?

910
00:57:27,750 --> 00:57:28,880
Pull yourself together.

911
00:57:32,850 --> 00:57:34,820
Why can't we marry
if we're not in love?

912
00:57:35,620 --> 00:57:37,460
- What?
- Why can't you marry...

913
00:57:37,460 --> 00:57:38,490
without love?

914
00:57:38,490 --> 00:57:40,530
Who says you have to marry
someone you love...

915
00:57:40,660 --> 00:57:42,160
when not every love
leads to marriage?

916
00:57:42,160 --> 00:57:43,700
What is this nonsense?

917
00:57:43,700 --> 00:57:45,530
Why would you marry without love?
What for?

918
00:57:45,530 --> 00:57:48,340
I'm asking why you must love someone
to marry her.

919
00:57:49,700 --> 00:57:50,710
Fine.

920
00:57:51,670 --> 00:57:53,010
Why are you thinking...

921
00:57:53,010 --> 00:57:54,610
about marrying someone
you don't even love?

922
00:57:57,480 --> 00:57:59,680
I may not love her,
but I might need the marriage.

923
00:58:00,920 --> 00:58:02,750
Why would you enter
into a marriage like that?

924
00:58:02,750 --> 00:58:04,290
Just live alone,
for crying out loud.

925
00:58:04,290 --> 00:58:06,320
Do that.
You're anti-marriage, after all.

926
00:58:09,460 --> 00:58:11,360
- "A marriage like that?"
- You heard me.

927
00:58:12,460 --> 00:58:14,530
As if I don't know
why Jung Bo A wants to marry you...

928
00:58:15,000 --> 00:58:17,700
and why you're considering
marrying her.

929
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:21,470
Actually, you're clueless.

930
00:58:21,470 --> 00:58:22,470
I know why.

931
00:58:22,470 --> 00:58:25,770
I knew you'd never understand,
no matter how hard you tried.

932
00:58:26,840 --> 00:58:28,040
But this is funny,

933
00:58:28,740 --> 00:58:31,010
how you're objecting
until you're red in the face.

934
00:58:31,010 --> 00:58:32,080
Because we're friends.

935
00:58:33,450 --> 00:58:35,180
I'm objecting because we're friends.

936
00:58:36,350 --> 00:58:37,390
Are you?

937
00:58:38,020 --> 00:58:39,050
Ji Hyuk.

938
00:58:41,090 --> 00:58:42,590
This isn't right at all.

939
00:58:45,860 --> 00:58:47,630
Hearing you talk made me realize...

940
00:58:49,500 --> 00:58:50,700
it's not a bad idea.

941
00:58:51,630 --> 00:58:53,870
Yes. I can do it.

942
00:58:54,640 --> 00:58:56,970
- What?
- This is why I didn't tell you.

943
00:58:57,040 --> 00:58:58,510
It's why I couldn't.

944
00:58:59,370 --> 00:59:00,740
It's not a topic for us.

945
00:59:01,710 --> 00:59:03,040
Because you...

946
00:59:04,110 --> 00:59:05,380
could never understand.

947
00:59:07,220 --> 00:59:08,280
Lee Ji Hyuk.

948
00:59:09,950 --> 00:59:11,420
Is this the extent
of our friendship?

949
00:59:14,420 --> 00:59:16,320
There are things
that can't be shared.

950
00:59:17,730 --> 00:59:18,860
There was.

951
00:59:20,230 --> 00:59:21,300
Between us, even.

952
00:59:22,030 --> 00:59:23,260
What does that mean?

953
00:59:27,440 --> 00:59:28,440
Take care.

954
00:59:59,130 --> 01:00:00,200
You're here.

955
01:00:00,570 --> 01:00:01,640
I'm here.

956
01:00:03,100 --> 01:00:04,110
Take a seat.

957
01:00:04,410 --> 01:00:05,410
Then we can...

958
01:00:07,210 --> 01:00:08,380
discuss our marriage.

959
01:00:18,950 --> 01:00:21,590
You've made up your mind, then.

960
01:00:24,590 --> 01:00:27,000
Some got married three days
after meeting on a blind date.

961
01:00:29,530 --> 01:00:30,730
Thank you.

962
01:00:33,170 --> 01:00:34,300
I feel reassured now.

963
01:00:35,370 --> 01:00:37,810
My future won't be as bleak.

964
01:00:39,040 --> 01:00:40,070
I feel the same.

965
01:00:41,280 --> 01:00:43,080
We're getting married
because we both have a need.

966
01:00:44,250 --> 01:00:46,650
Let's make this a win-win.

967
01:00:49,350 --> 01:00:50,790
Do we have to...

968
01:00:51,050 --> 01:00:53,250
sign a contract or something
before we get started?

969
01:00:54,520 --> 01:00:55,820
That sounds horrific.

970
01:00:56,390 --> 01:00:59,260
We're getting married for real.
It's not a contractual marriage.

971
01:01:01,260 --> 01:01:03,560
You must have a boundary, though.

972
01:01:05,300 --> 01:01:07,700
You seem to have one.

973
01:01:08,270 --> 01:01:09,470
A boundary.

974
01:01:13,740 --> 01:01:14,810
Tell me.

975
01:01:15,210 --> 01:01:17,610
My father and I...

976
01:01:17,780 --> 01:01:19,910
want you to work at our company.

977
01:01:20,520 --> 01:01:21,620
That's the biggest thing.

978
01:01:23,120 --> 01:01:24,190
Then...

979
01:01:26,390 --> 01:01:27,590
here are my conditions.

980
01:01:44,770 --> 01:01:45,970
Are you nervous?

981
01:01:50,450 --> 01:01:52,450
I didn't think I'd meet him so soon.

982
01:02:13,000 --> 01:02:14,670
Welcome. He's waiting for you.

983
01:02:15,400 --> 01:02:16,470
I'm Lee Ji Hyuk.

984
01:02:17,310 --> 01:02:18,840
He's the chief secretary.

985
01:02:19,270 --> 01:02:21,610
Chief Secretary Cha Mun Seok
and Mr. Kim, the chauffeur.

986
01:02:22,940 --> 01:02:24,650
You have keys in your pocket.

987
01:02:25,650 --> 01:02:26,680
Yes.

988
01:02:26,680 --> 01:02:29,020
They make a noise.
Leave them with him.

989
01:02:30,620 --> 01:02:31,650
Okay.

990
01:02:33,620 --> 01:02:34,690
Come this way.

991
01:02:37,730 --> 01:02:39,690
Nice to meet you, sir.
I'm Lee Ji Hyuk.

992
01:02:41,400 --> 01:02:42,460
I'm Jung Ho Yeong.

993
01:02:42,860 --> 01:02:44,330
I'm Bo A's father.

994
01:02:44,870 --> 01:02:46,130
Please speak freely.

995
01:02:46,400 --> 01:02:48,570
I can't do that
until the handshake's over at least.

996
01:02:51,440 --> 01:02:52,710
Let's sit down.

997
01:02:57,410 --> 01:02:59,350
There's no need
to feel awkward or uncomfortable.

998
01:02:59,980 --> 01:03:01,250
That goes for now and in the future.

999
01:03:02,680 --> 01:03:03,890
The truth is,

1000
01:03:04,950 --> 01:03:06,220
we're not dating.

1001
01:03:06,490 --> 01:03:07,520
I know that.

1002
01:03:08,120 --> 01:03:09,960
I know why you want to get married.

1003
01:03:11,490 --> 01:03:13,390
I like you, still.

1004
01:03:14,360 --> 01:03:17,000
You're just the right man for Bo A.

1005
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:21,640
Don't take it to heart.

1006
01:03:22,270 --> 01:03:23,670
Rumors about me have spread,

1007
01:03:23,670 --> 01:03:25,740
and no one at our level
will date me.

1008
01:03:27,210 --> 01:03:28,940
I know that much.

1009
01:03:30,580 --> 01:03:33,150
Does love come first
when it comes to marriage?

1010
01:03:34,080 --> 01:03:35,120
No.

1011
01:03:35,780 --> 01:03:38,790
I married my wife
after we'd met just three times,

1012
01:03:39,150 --> 01:03:40,660
and we're still happily married.

1013
01:03:42,190 --> 01:03:43,190
Right.

1014
01:03:45,090 --> 01:03:46,760
Bo A will give you...

1015
01:03:46,760 --> 01:03:49,830
a few dates to choose from
for the wedding.

1016
01:03:51,100 --> 01:03:52,870
I'd like it to be sooner
rather than later.

1017
01:03:54,740 --> 01:03:56,040
How about two weeks from now?

1018
01:04:13,450 --> 01:04:15,820
(Haneul Construction)

1019
01:04:16,690 --> 01:04:18,390
I guess
Mr. Kim picked up your car for you.

1020
01:04:20,760 --> 01:04:23,800
I'll go home with my father.

1021
01:04:24,170 --> 01:04:26,130
- Get in the car.
- Okay.

1022
01:04:37,610 --> 01:04:39,650
Call once you have
your parents' permission.

1023
01:04:39,980 --> 01:04:42,520
That will kick-start
the preparations.

1024
01:04:43,450 --> 01:04:45,290
Okay. I'll be in touch.

1025
01:05:04,970 --> 01:05:06,040
(What can I do for you?)

1026
01:05:06,640 --> 01:05:08,610
Text Ji Wan and Su Bin.

1027
01:05:10,310 --> 01:05:11,910
What do you mean...

1028
01:05:12,450 --> 01:05:13,550
you want to change the theme?

1029
01:05:13,750 --> 01:05:15,980
I have an idea.

1030
01:05:17,990 --> 01:05:19,550
I'm going to bring on a guest.

1031
01:05:20,190 --> 01:05:21,220
A guest?

1032
01:05:25,060 --> 01:05:26,890
(Oldest brother)

1033
01:05:27,830 --> 01:05:29,230
Be home by 6 p.m.

1034
01:05:29,500 --> 01:05:30,560
What?

1035
01:05:31,170 --> 01:05:33,430
I have something important to say.
Be there.

1036
01:05:35,870 --> 01:05:36,870
I got caught?

1037
01:05:37,510 --> 01:05:38,770
He found out?

1038
01:05:40,270 --> 01:05:41,480
Yes.

1039
01:05:42,640 --> 01:05:43,980
It was too stressful.

1040
01:05:44,780 --> 01:05:46,550
I'll come clean...

1041
01:05:47,250 --> 01:05:48,680
and get smacked just once.

1042
01:05:50,150 --> 01:05:52,390
But Ji Hyuk's punches really hurt.

1043
01:06:06,370 --> 01:06:09,340
What's the occasion
that all three of you...

1044
01:06:09,370 --> 01:06:11,870
came home around the same time?

1045
01:06:12,140 --> 01:06:14,880
It has been a while
since we gathered for a meal.

1046
01:06:15,180 --> 01:06:17,510
Ji Hyuk told us to come home early.

1047
01:06:17,610 --> 01:06:18,880
He texted us.

1048
01:06:19,480 --> 01:06:21,580
You did, Ji Hyuk? What for?

1049
01:06:22,450 --> 01:06:23,850
Is something going on?

1050
01:06:24,620 --> 01:06:25,790
Let's finish dinner first.

1051
01:06:26,520 --> 01:06:28,520
Tell us now.

1052
01:06:28,820 --> 01:06:30,190
What's going on?

1053
01:06:30,990 --> 01:06:33,230
Why did you want
Ji Wan and Su Bin here too?

1054
01:06:33,990 --> 01:06:35,160
Are you in trouble?

1055
01:06:35,260 --> 01:06:36,300
- No.
- No.

1056
01:06:36,300 --> 01:06:38,570
No. I have something to tell you.

1057
01:06:39,530 --> 01:06:41,540
Are you free this Thursday
around lunchtime?

1058
01:06:42,400 --> 01:06:43,470
Yes.

1059
01:06:44,170 --> 01:06:45,540
Mother, you must be free.

1060
01:06:45,870 --> 01:06:48,010
You two. Free up a few hours
even if you're busy.

1061
01:06:48,580 --> 01:06:49,610
- Okay.
- Okay.

1062
01:06:50,110 --> 01:06:53,710
Ji Hyuk.
Tell us what it's about first.

1063
01:06:54,580 --> 01:06:55,620
I'd like you...

1064
01:06:56,520 --> 01:06:59,390
to meet the parents
of the woman I'm going to marry.

1065
01:07:02,360 --> 01:07:03,360
I'm...

1066
01:07:04,790 --> 01:07:05,830
getting married.

1067
01:07:58,050 --> 01:08:00,880
(Our Golden Days)

1068
01:08:01,250 --> 01:08:03,750
I'm not asking
for permission to marry.

1069
01:08:03,820 --> 01:08:07,690
When did you schedule
the wedding for, then?

1070
01:08:07,990 --> 01:08:10,020
You held back and didn't get angry.

1071
01:08:10,360 --> 01:08:11,660
It didn't bruise your ego?

1072
01:08:11,790 --> 01:08:15,000
I look forward to
a new and impressive design.

1073
01:08:15,200 --> 01:08:16,860
How about 30,000 dollars as a fee?

1074
01:08:17,570 --> 01:08:18,630
I'm getting married.

1075
01:08:18,630 --> 01:08:19,730
